Carson Pirie Scott and Co said the TaxReform Act of 1986, which repealed investment tax credits, hada negative impact of 22 cts a share on earnings for the yearended January 31.    Earlier, Carson reported yearly per-share earnings of 1.83dlrs, down from 1.86 dlrs a year ago. Average shares increasedto 10.2 mln from 9.9 mln a year earlier. Sales gained to 1.41billion dlrs from 1.30 billion dlrs.    Carson said it was "extremely optimistic about improvedprofit performance in 1987."    It said in the first half of 1987 it hopes to reduceseasonal-type losses sustained in the 1986 first and secondquarters.    The company said that in early April its Oak Brook HillsHotel and Conference Center in suburban Chicago will open underits management. Provisions for startup expenses have been made,it added. Reuter&#3;